1
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:35,000
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:37,800
[Episode 16]

3
00:01:38,229 --> 00:01:39,830
I, Tao Baohua, am the only one

4
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:42,030
that is allowed to beat my son.

5
00:01:43,009 --> 00:01:43,700
No one else

6
00:01:44,789 --> 00:01:46,280
can lay a finger on you.

7
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,229
Should I come back again tomorrow?

8
00:01:49,229 --> 00:01:50,729
Why wouldn't you come back?

9
00:01:50,729 --> 00:01:54,479
[Business Time: 5:30 a.m.]

10
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:53,800
If I come back a few more times,

11
00:01:54,259 --> 00:01:55,640
our family's business

12
00:01:56,370 --> 00:01:57,500
will be ruined by me.

13
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:02,120
Don't worry.

14
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,730
It will all be yours eventually.

15
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,380
Whether it's ruined or not,

16
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:11,150
it's up to you.

17
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:13,610
Dad,

18
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,060
actually,

19
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:17,910
I'm used to it.

20
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:20,370
You're used to it?

21
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,770
What do you mean?

22
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,490
Actually, I'm just a lousy performer.

23
00:02:28,530 --> 00:02:29,530
Over the years,

24
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:33,410
I've gotten used to
how people from outside

25
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:34,160
treat me.

26
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:46,970
Liangliang.

27
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:50,380
Let me just ask you one thing.

28
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:56,020
So you can just endure something like this

29
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:58,700
and keep enduring it without giving up?

30
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,230
I've made up my mind.

31
00:03:04,530 --> 00:03:05,530
I can do it myself.

32
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:08,750
No matter how hard it is,

33
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:12,200
I still have to stick to the path
I've chosen.

34
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:29,560
I got it.

35
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:35,290
Thanks, Dad.

36
00:03:35,410 --> 00:03:38,090
[Business Time: 5:30 a.m.]

37
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:58,090
I feel like I'm cursed.

38
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,250
I have such bad luck.

39
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,660
My saxophone fell and broke.

40
00:04:02,470 --> 00:04:03,270
What's wrong?

41
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:04,840
So your saxophone is broken?

42
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,390
Well,

43
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,340
I accidentally dropped it,

44
00:04:07,340 --> 00:04:08,740
and now it's leaking air.

45
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:13,870
No, no, no!

46
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:14,830
Stop playing it!

47
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:16,190
Just spare me.

48
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,990
I have an orchestra audition
in a few days.

49
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:20,240
[Endeavor]

50
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,060
I can't borrow one from others.

51
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,320
Who would lend it to me?

52
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,440
You're still going to the audition?

53
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:29,730
[Endeavor]

54
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,790
I have to.

55
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,740
Even if all orchestra auditions
in the world were rigged,

56
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:26,500
I would still have to try.

57
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:27,420
When the results are out,

58
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:28,270
my name will be there,

59
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,730
and they'll feel ashamed.

60
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,980
How should I repair it?

61
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,400
You're driving me crazy.

62
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:48,190
This money is enough to repair it, huh?

63
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:54,330
I'm lending it to you.

64
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,720
Just repair your saxophone properly.

65
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,680
This sounds like

66
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,090
it has a great mission.

67
00:05:03,570 --> 00:05:04,620
As screenwriters,

68
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:05,800
you can make so much money, huh?

69
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,540
Where did you

70
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:07,980
get this money?

71
00:05:08,130 --> 00:05:09,370
None of your business.

72
00:05:09,370 --> 00:05:11,230
I bought a lottery ticket and won.

73
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:15,980
I didn't say you wouldn't
have to return the money.

74
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,190
I also didn't say
I wouldn't return the money.

75
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:19,870
I just think...

76
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,360
Just take it.

77
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:23,190
You are from Beijing anyway.

78
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:23,870
If there's a penny less

79
00:05:23,870 --> 00:05:25,180
when you return the money,

80
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:26,040
I will go to your house

81
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,300
and ask your mom for it.

82
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:27,770
Fine.

83
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,620
You can ask my mom, my dad

84
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,080
or whoever you want for it.

85
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,420
But this time,

86
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:34,370
you've really done me a big favor.

87
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:35,730
Thank you, Xu.

88
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:36,290
No.

89
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,100
Thank you,

90
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,070
Mr. Xu.

91
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,070
I'll go make a call now

92
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,070
to contact the parts supplier.

93
00:05:42,070 --> 00:05:42,630
Just go.

94
00:05:42,630 --> 00:05:43,300
Well...

95
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:46,100
Dear friend, I'll return your favor later.

96
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:46,960
Thanks, Mr. Xu!

97
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:00,570
Honey!

98
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:01,940
Honey!

99
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:03,620
Hurry up!

100
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:04,250
What's wrong?

101
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:04,980
Look at this.

102
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:11,060
Well, what a broad smile you have.

103
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:12,400
W-Where did you get

104
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,570
so much money?

105
00:06:13,810 --> 00:06:15,480
Your son sent it to us.

106
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:16,710
Our son sent it to us?

107
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:19,390
He also wrote on the postscript

108
00:06:19,390 --> 00:06:20,920
that we should buy two sets

109
00:06:20,950 --> 00:06:22,220
of nice clothes.

110
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,490
How much is this?

111
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,420
5,000 yuan.

112
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:25,280
5,000 yuan?

113
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:28,620
Using 5,000 yuan
to buy two sets of clothes?

114
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:30,710
Are they dragon robes?

115
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:31,360
Well,

116
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:33,540
he didn't ask us to spend it all.

117
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:38,970
I got it.

118
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,010
This boy...

119
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:46,930
is trying to make me angry on purpose.

120
00:06:47,770 --> 00:06:49,659
You are so narrow-minded.

121
00:06:50,370 --> 00:06:50,950
This boy

122
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:51,800
sent so much money to us.

123
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,430
He's being filial, you know?

124
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,240
Being filial?

125
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:54,950
Besides,

126
00:06:55,450 --> 00:06:56,800
this 5,000 yuan can prove

127
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,360
that he is doing quite well

128
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,060
in Beijing right now.

129
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,440
If he's really doing well, that's nice.

130
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,220
Could it be that

131
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:06,300
he is not on the right track?

132
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,260
Don't think of everything

133
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,390
in such a...

134
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:12,690
As his father,

135
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:14,470
how could you say that about your son?

136
00:07:14,470 --> 00:07:16,190
-I'm worried about him. Why can't I...
-You are not...

137
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:17,480
Y-Your son isn't

138
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,300
someone like that.

139
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:20,040
Besides, what kind of place is Beijing?

140
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,390
Beijing is heaven.

141
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:24,140
Alright.

142
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:25,500
We'll look on the bright side.

143
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:25,960
Okay?

144
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:30,060
What should we do now?

145
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:31,060
Let's do as he said

146
00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:33,020
and go buy some clothes.

147
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:34,370
Let's go buy some clothes.

148
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:35,370
-Let's go!
-Come on!

149
00:07:35,370 --> 00:07:37,100
Let's eat at a restaurant, too.

150
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:39,810
I'm tired of cooking.

151
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:43,860
Let's find the best restaurant.

152
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,180
Yes, let's find one with

153
00:07:45,180 --> 00:07:46,070
a really bright storefront.

154
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:47,250
We'll order the most expensive dishes.

155
00:07:47,250 --> 00:07:47,620
Yes!

156
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:48,480
Is that okay?

157
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:50,070
Then the owner of this restaurant

158
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,670
will be overjoyed, won't he?

159
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:53,240
At night... At night, he'll be so happy

160
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,450
even in his dreams.

161
00:07:55,659 --> 00:07:56,659
Great.

162
00:07:58,159 --> 00:07:58,720
What are you looking at?

163
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,520
You know what?

164
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:04,100
We should buy you a woolen coat.

165
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:05,660
We'll buy...

166
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:07,060
And a pair of riding boots

167
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:08,290
with heels.

168
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,360
What do you think?

169
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,420
You know what?

170
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,240
A few days ago, I really saw one

171
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,480
at the department store.

172
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,680
-It was very beautiful.
-So you want it?

173
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,010
I'll satisfy you.

174
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,520
Okay.

175
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:20,800
Let's go.

176
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,330
Let's go.

177
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:26,810
What's wrong?

178
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:28,270
Let's go.

179
00:08:28,570 --> 00:08:29,570
Let's not do this.

180
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:31,960
For us,

181
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:33,809
just talking about it is enough.

182
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:36,200
I-I still want to deposit this money

183
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,179
into his...

184
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:39,820
his previous bankbook.

185
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:42,500
With this, the bank balance will be almost

186
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,480
10,000 yuan.

187
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:45,600
Oh, you're...

188
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,360
such a good mother.

189
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:56,410
We're so lucky to have you in this family.

190
00:08:58,740 --> 00:08:59,650
Being with me,

191
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:01,980
you've suffered a lot.

192
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,930
That's not true.

193
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:04,490
How about this?

194
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,790
We'll deposit the money in the bank
for our kid first.

195
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:07,920
Let's do as you said.

196
00:09:08,370 --> 00:09:09,520
When I get my salary,

197
00:09:10,870 --> 00:09:11,800
I'll definitely

198
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,500
buy you a new outfit.

199
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:15,050
Is that okay?

200
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:15,390
Okay.

201
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,920
I feel more at ease spending your money.

202
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,530
I'll go deposit this in the bank now.

203
00:09:19,530 --> 00:09:20,040
Just go.

204
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,170
Thank you so much.

205
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,270
So this is the Seasons Change Hostel

206
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:52,330
you've mentioned?

207
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,030
Yes.

208
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:55,200
But we still have to go further in.

209
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,650
Alright. I'm not going in.

210
00:09:58,650 --> 00:09:59,840
I'll just drop you off here.

211
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,320
Mr. Chu,

212
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,110
thank you.

213
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,720
You're saying this again.

214
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,770
There's nothing to thank me for.

215
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:06,830
You're excellent,

216
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,560
so the director chose you.

217
00:10:08,740 --> 00:10:09,800
I know

218
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:11,500
without your help,

219
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:13,720
I wouldn't have gotten this role.

220
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,190
This role isn't too big or too small.

221
00:10:17,410 --> 00:10:18,810
It's just a normal favor.

222
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:20,170
If it's helpful

223
00:10:20,170 --> 00:10:21,390
for your acting career,

224
00:10:21,390 --> 00:10:23,120
I can do even more in the future.

225
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,320
You've already helped me quite enough.

226
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,520
I have to work hard by myself from now on.

227
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,970
Let me give you a little advice.

228
00:10:32,470 --> 00:10:33,200
You'd better

229
00:10:33,410 --> 00:10:35,220
listen more to experienced people.

230
00:10:35,220 --> 00:10:37,420
This way, you can avoid taking detours.

231
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:39,460
Yes.

232
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,170
Bye, Mr. Chu.

233
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:42,940
Bye.

234
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:59,370
[The Late Love,
written by He Sheng & Xu Shengli]

235
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:01,740
[Dimly, a shadow was shaking.]

236
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:02,400
[Night Cat
walked into the factory gently.]

237
00:11:02,430 --> 00:11:02,960
[A moment later,
there was a terrible scream.]

238
00:11:34,710 --> 00:11:36,830
[Abandoned]

239
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:58,070
[It kept crawling and staring.]

240
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:06,910
[The Late Love,
written by He Sheng & Xu Shengli]

241
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:27,930
[To the General Editorial Office
of Jinnan Film Studio]

242
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:32,820
Good luck!

243
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,810
Xu Shengli, the screenwriter.

244
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:40,410
Every time I pass by here,

245
00:12:40,650 --> 00:12:41,650
I always feel that

246
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,230
before pursuing my dreams,

247
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:46,190
I still have to survive first.

248
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,620
You have to consider it
the other way around.

249
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:51,190
This is also a reminder that

250
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:53,680
all paths will meet again eventually.

251
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,050
Definitely.

252
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:06,040
[End-of-term Performance
of Beijing Conservatory of Music]

253
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,060
Zhuang Zhuang.

254
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:05,780
Give it a try.

255
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,630
There's still a little bit
of the original track

256
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:09,490
which I really couldn't cover up.

257
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:10,580
So they're mine?

258
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:16,920
[Small Auditorium]

259
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:14,720
Thank you, Xu Shengli.

260
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,340
Not at all.

261
00:13:15,940 --> 00:13:16,860
This is the first time

262
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,520
I've had my own backing track.

263
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:20,440
In the future,

264
00:13:20,940 --> 00:13:21,750
you'll be

265
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:22,480
accompanied

266
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,410
by a whole band,

267
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:24,230
right in here.

268
00:13:33,170 --> 00:13:34,360
Affected by the

269
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:36,370
strong cold air mass from Siberia,

270
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:38,440
North China will recently experience

271
00:13:37,460 --> 00:13:40,560
[Hengtian Non-Staple Food]

272
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:39,500
a large-scale

273
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:41,010
sharp drop in temperature.

274
00:13:41,010 --> 00:13:43,870
Many places
have seen the first snow of this winter.

275
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:49,080
Repairing range hoods!

276
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,650
As an important city

277
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:51,550
in North China,

278
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,600
Beijing is the first to feel

279
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,060
the power of this cold air.

280
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,650
Meanwhile,

281
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,240
some areas in Northwest China,

282
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,100
as well as Henan, Hebei and other places,

283
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,700
have also ushered in snowy weather.

284
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,900
In Hebei, from Zhangjiakou in the north

285
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,170
to Handan in the south,

286
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:06,900
a large area is covered by snow.

287
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,700
This snowfall

288
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,050
has caused some highways

289
00:14:09,050 --> 00:14:09,980
to be temporarily closed.

290
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:10,840
Railway transportation

291
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:11,410
